description:
&lt;p&gt;18 Week Support are currently seeking a Patient Safety Lead to join our team on a Substantive basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a really diverse and interesting role in which the post-holder will support the Head of Governance &amp; Risk to develop and support ongoing improvements in patient safety, quality and risk management across the organisation. Key responsibilities of the role are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Head of Governance and Chief Nurse with the implementation of risk management strategies, policies and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To support the Head of Governance &amp; Risk in the development, implementation and driving of Patient Safety agenda as part of the wider Integrated Governance Strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide advice, training, support on a range of quality and patient safety issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage a learning culture ensuring patient safety and continuous quality improvement are key drivers in practice development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day to day management of Datix Integrated Risk Management System&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the main interface with the Incident Reporting System&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18 Week Support is an RTT support provider which supports NHS Trusts with meeting their RTT pathways and 18-week waiting time targets. Like the NHS, patient care is at the centre of everything we do, and our clinical teams are dedicated to ensuring excellent patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an ethical and transparent organisation that is committed to the NHS and the delivery of high-quality care, and to helping NHS Trusts reduce RTT waiting times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pension contribution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Private health insurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;25 days’ Annual Leave + Bank Holidays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Induction, CPD and career opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicant Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educated to degree level (or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use of Datix Risk Management system 4+ years working in an acute hospital setting within a clinical governance role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of incident and complaint investigation; identifying lessons learnt with clinicians, and writing up investigations/complaint responses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RCA skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use and application of information technology systems including effective internet use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical governance and risk management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Essential I.T. (EIT) skills or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please see enclosed job description for full post details.&lt;/p&gt;
